# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Content Studio — Environment Variables
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the values you need.
#
#   cp .env.example .env.local
#
# The app works out of the box with NO env vars set.
# All variables below are OPTIONAL and enable enhanced features.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Web Search ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# By default, the Research Agent uses DuckDuckGo (no key needed).
# To use a different provider, set one of the following:

# Google Custom Search (https://developers.google.com/custom-search/v1/overview)
# GOOGLE_SEARCH_API_KEY=
# GOOGLE_SEARCH_ENGINE_ID=

# SerpAPI (https://serpapi.com/)
# SERPAPI_KEY=

# ── LLM Integration (future) ────────────────────────────────
# To replace the rule-based writer/editor with an LLM, set one of:

# OpenAI (https://platform.openai.com/api-keys)
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Anthropic (https://console.anthropic.com/)
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ── App Configuration ────────────────────────────────────────
# Base URL (auto-detected in most deployments, override if needed)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000
